  "market_context": "NQ1! on 25/8/2023. Asia session formed a consolidation range around 15000–15060. Approaching the London session with price testing the lower boundary, setting up a classic cross-session AMD profile.",
  "key_observation": "Asia accumulated within a defined range, London manipulated by sweeping the low and displacing aggressively back into the range, signaling that New York would distribute higher toward standard deviation targets and old highs.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified Asia session behavior as accumulation/consolidation and marked out the range.",
    "Observed London session producing an aggressive sweep of the Asia range low.",
    "Confirmed manipulation (not continuation) by aggressive displacement back into the range rather than a retracement.",
    "Anchored standard deviation projection from the London manipulation low to the high that created it.",
    "Identified targets to the upside: a failure swing just before the -2 standard deviation and an old high resting nearby.",
    "Marked the London manipulation leg and waited for the New York session to deliver distribution.",
    "Noted a fair value gap formed just prior to New York as a potential entry POI, with stop on the manipulation low and target at the failure swing (low-hanging fruit).",
    "Tracked price as it retested the breaker, displaced higher, and delivered into both the failure swing and the old highs."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price delivered to the low-hanging fruit failure swing as well as the old high, hitting both the -2 and -2.5 standard deviation projections off the London manipulation leg.",
  "lessons": "When Asia accumulates and London sweeps with aggressive displacement back into the range, expect New York to distribute toward standard deviation targets and old highs. Pair AMD across sessions with standard deviation projections for high-probability targets.",
